						               													<description>THE WORLD IS FIGHTING A PANDEMIC.&amp;#10;BUT YOU NEED FOOD AND TOILET PAPER  TO STAY AT HOME.&amp;#10;This fun game is about fighting a pandemic and stereotypes people see these times.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You play as usual citizens and have to survive. You need to stay at home, but if you don't have resources you need to go outside risking to get a virus.&amp;#10;- Accumulate food and toilet paper&amp;#10;- Hide if you are ill&amp;#10;- Steal food&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To start, all players take a character card and a corresponding lucky card. All player cards are face up.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Rounds: Every round is a new day. Each turn, you can choose to go outside or stay at home, use food, and toilet paper, or take cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If decided to go outside, you can take a minimum of 1 and a  maximum of 2 cards&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to prevent the disease:&amp;#10;Use your mask before you start drawing cards. Then if you draw a virus, you will not get ill. Use sanitizer if you get a virus (it kills the virus). Use your lucky card (always helps) as a last resort.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to manage the disease:&amp;#10;If you are infected you have 2 options:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Reveal (change state to not hiding the virus) then you have to call a doctor (use DOCTOR CARD) 3 turns in a row.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Hide &amp;ndash; act as a usual citizen but an Inspection card reveals  your disease, so you have to reveal being ill and start treatment. After that, the virus is discarded.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;ANY player can reveal that another one is ill (only if that player has a virus).  The revealed player has to start treatment.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;IMPORTANT&amp;#10;VIRUS + VIRUS = DEATH&amp;#10;LOSE EVEN IF YOU ARE IN TREATMENT&amp;#10;IF A PLAYER DIES &amp;ndash; THE VIRUS RETURNS TO THE DECK&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to win:&amp;#10;When the deck ends and no live players have a virus &amp;ndash; they all win.&amp;#10;When the deck ends and at least 1 player has a virus &amp;ndash; they try to survive till the end of resources.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
